<h1>Find tips to provide your cat with with the best care possible!</h1>
<h3>Balanced Diet: </h3>
<p>
    Feed your cat a high-quality diet formulated for their life stage and health needs. Ensure access
    to fresh water at all times.
</p>
<h3>Litter Box Maintenance: </h3>
<p>
    Keep the litter box clean and odor-free by scooping it daily and changing the litter
    regularly. Place multiple litter boxes in different areas of the house for multi-cat households.
</p>
<h3>Scratching Posts: </h3>
<p>
    Provide scratching posts or pads to satisfy your cat's natural scratching behavior and prevent
    damage to furniture.
</p>
<h3>Regular Veterinary Visits: </h3>
<p>
    Schedule routine veterinary check-ups for vaccinations, dental care, and preventive
    health measures. Monitor your cat's weight and behavior for any changes.
</p>
<h3>Enrichment Activites: </h3>
<p>
    Offer toys, climbing structures, and hiding spots to stimulate your cat's physical and
    mental well-being. Rotate toys regularly to keep them engaged.
</p>
<h3>Grooming: </h3>
<p>
    Brush your cat's coat to reduce shedding and hairballs, trim their nails as needed, and clean their
    ears and teeth regularly to maintain oral health.
</p>
<h3>Indoor Safety: </h3>
<p>
    Ensure your home is cat-proofed to prevent accidents and ingestion of harmful substances. Keep
    toxic plants, small objects, and electrical cords out of reach.
</p>
